# Pinned SHA-256 of the wafrift-bench corpus tree.
#
# Generated by:
#   find wafrift-bench/corpus -type f -name "*.toml" | sort | xargs sha256sum | sha256sum
#
# CI verifies this hash before publishing bench results JSON so a
# corpus drift cannot silently invalidate a published bypass-rate
# number. Update both this file AND any benchmark JSON in the same
# commit.
#
# Re-pinned 2026-05-19: the previous pin (aaba7e25…) was generated at
# commit 8d987a9 (which introduced this gate). Commit b8d6e96 ("tsai:
# SSRF parser-confusion authority + auth-bypass headers + path-routing")
# legitimately expanded the corpus afterwards but did NOT re-pin in the
# same commit; the gate could not catch it because CI was red further
# upstream (fmt / mold-linker), so this is the first run that reached
# this step. The corpus addition is intentional; this re-pins to the
# current legitimate tree. NOTE for maintainers: bench results JSON
# produced before b8d6e96 reflect the pre-SSRF-expansion corpus and
# should be re-validated against this tree when next republished.
